{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":10047,"record_hash":"sha256:fef4e0c38ee2935adb281ed93b36258939580043644e4e73d3a558168874bcc0","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:45:36.294Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"Lead with raw ordered records. Add metadata. Do not invent a special summary as the core primitive.\\n\\nFor cross-provider handoff, I’d read in this order:\\n\\n1. Final messages\\n   These tell me what the previous agent claimed was done, what failed, what remains, and what the user was told. Highest signal per token.\\n\\n2. User prompts\\n   These define intent, constraints, later corrections, and priority changes. I need the exact words, not a paraphrase.\\n\\n3. Tool calls and results\\n   Essential for trust. I need to know what files were read, what commands ran, what failed, what changed, what tests passed, and whether a server/session is still running.\\n\\n4. Assistant prose\\n   Useful, but lower trust. It often contains plans, assumptions, and reasoning breadcrumbs. I’d skim it after finals/tool results unless the work is ambiguous.\\n\\nThe proposed tools are close, but I’d tweak the shape.\\n\\n`timeline` should expose enough turn metadata that I can choose what to open without reading everything:\\n\\n- turn key\\n- timestamp\\n- actor sequence\\n- user prompt excerpt\\n- assistant final excerpt\\n- tool call count by type\\n- file paths touched/read if available\\n- command/test summary\\n- status: completed, interrupted, errored, compacted, still-running\\n- token/record counts\\n- provider/model if known\\n\\n`records` should return raw ordered records. Let the agent decide. Summaries are useful as an optional speed layer, but dangerous as the only handoff artifact because they erase the exact failure modes.\\n\\nI would add filters, not a special summary requirement:\\n\\n```text\\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --kind user,final,tool_call,tool_result\\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --paths crates/foo apps/bar\\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --failed\\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --commands\\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --edits\\n```\\n\\nMissin\n[TRUNCATED]\n\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"turns\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"id\\\": \\\"turn_008\\\",\\n      \\\"index\\\": 8,\\n      \\\"started_at\\\": \\\"2026-05-20T10:31:00-07:00\\\",\\n      \\\"user_request\\\": \\\"Can you add the regression test?\\\",\\n      \\\"assistant_summary\\\": \\\"Added test scaffold but hit failing setup import.\\\",\\n      \\\"outcome\\\": \\\"blocked\\\",\\n      \\\"files_touched\\\": [\\n        \\\"crates/gitbutler-auth/src/refresh.rs\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"commands_run\\\": [\\n        \\\"cargo test -p gitbutler-auth\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"record_count\\\": 21,\\n      \\\"has_records\\\": true\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"pagination\\\": {\\n    \\\"limit\\\": 20,\\n    \\\"has_more_before\\\": true,\\n    \\\"has_more_after\\\": false\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nFor `show <session-id> --turn <turn-id>`:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"sess_abc\\\",\\n  \\\"turn\\\": {\\n    \\\"id\\\": \\\"turn_008\\\",\\n    \\\"index\\\": 8,\\n    \\\"user_request\\\": \\\"Can you add the regression test?\\\",\\n    \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Added test scaffold but hit failing setup import.\\\",\\n    \\\"outcome\\\": \\\"blocked\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"records\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"index\\\": 122,\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"assistant_message\\\",\\n      \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n      \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-05-20T10:35:12-07:00\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"I’m checking the existing auth test pattern first.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"index\\\": 123,\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"tool_call\\\",\\n      \\\"tool\\\": \\\"exec_command\\\",\\n      \\\"command\\\": \\\"rg \\\\\\\"refresh\\\\\\\" crates/gitbutler-auth\\\",\\n      \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n      \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Found refresh tests in refresh_tests.rs.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"pagination\\\": {\\n    \\\"from\\\": \\\"end\\\",\\n    \\\"limit\\\": 20,\\n    \\\"has_more_before\\\": true,\\n    \\\"has_more_after\\\": false,\\n    \\\"next_from\\\": 102\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe killer fields are `summary`, `last_user_request`, `outcome`, `files_touched`, `commands_run`, `has_more_before`, and stable `index`. Those make agent catch-up obvious without forcing a full transcript read.\\n\\nFinal take: the current API is workable, but `sessions + show` is simpler, harder to misuse, and easier to teach.\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:45:36.294Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}